The Chronicle Mthabisi Tshuma, Showbiz Reporter IF you are a lover of luxury bags including wallets, handbags and suitcases, then Royal Infinity is the ideal place that you should visit. <img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-606901" src="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2022/05/Bags-2.jpg" alt="" width="680" height="380" srcset="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2022/05/Bags-2.jpg 680w, https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2022/05/Bags-2-360x200.jpg 360w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" /> A pride of Bulawayo, Royal Infinity is a brand that specialises in the design and distribution of bags ranging from wallets, purses, tote bags, hobo bags, satchels, bucket bags, facile frame bags, structured cases/box bags, barrel/duffle bags, drawstring bags, messenger bags, frame, camera, backpacks, trapezoids, shoulder bags, weekender and luggage bags among other types of bags. The bags are designed locally in Belmont while others are produced by designers in Turkey and China whom the company partnered with. <img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-606898" src="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2022/05/Bags-3.jpg" alt="" width="680" height="380" srcset="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2022/05/Bags-3.jpg 680w, https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2022/05/Bags-3-360x200.jpg 360w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" /> Established in June 2020, the fashion brand has been focusing on ladies and recently launched the men’s range. Royal Infinity founder and creative director Mercy Mabiza said: “Our vision is that our end products should respect the identities of individual clientele with customer acquisition being our priority. We aim to provide merchandise that customers are proud to carry. Our models are unique – with both an indigenous and exotic feel as we also incorporate various designers from across the globe in our range from Zimbabwean, Turkish, Italian and Asian.” <img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-606897" src="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2022/05/Bags-4.jpg" alt="" width="680" height="380" srcset="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2022/05/Bags-4.jpg 680w, https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2022/05/Bags-4-360x200.jpg 360w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" /> Mabiza said materials used during production include Genuine Leather, faux leather, suede, synthetics (PU, PVC, Ultrasuede), straw, lace, canvas, satin, silk, velvet, African print and burlap among others. “The bags are of great quality and affordable. The brand name brings to light how I am passionate about women’s empowerment as I view all women as queens. Queens are associated with royalty and the dream and hope are to see the brand growing till infinity. The dream is to build an empire and to grow the brand,” she said. Royal Infinity operates an online store with a website and social media pages which all collectively work to serve the clients timeously. <img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-606894" src="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2022/05/Bags-5.jpg" alt="" width="680" height="380" srcset="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2022/05/Bags-5.jpg 680w, https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2022/05/Bags-5-360x200.jpg 360w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" /> “We also have a physical showroom located in the Bulawayo CBD. We have primarily curated this showroom which is an artistic room, to display all our merchandise. It provides an intimate and personalised shopping experience for all our clients. When you visit our showroom, you can opt for home delivery instead of carrying out. “Our goal is to create experiential environments that will fulfill customers in new and innovative ways. We have since maintained the online platform and presence and are encouraging online shopping.” – @mthabisi_mthire   